{
  "texts": [
    "We can then marginalize out the blunt parameters",
    "to extract the sharp (that is, well-constrained) parameters.",
    "As a simple example, consider a system with a clean Einstein ring and no other data.",
    "In this example s as the enclosed mass and b as the radial profile are a possible parameter separation.",
    "Suppose, however, that we use a different parametrization that mixes sharp and blunt -say we take = (1, 2) where 1 is a power-law slope and 2 is a normalization -and marginalize out the normalization."
  ]
}